\section{מבוא: סוכני בינה מלאכותית ומהפכת הבריאות}
\label{sec:introduction}

\subsection{הנוף הנוכחי של אתגרי שירותי הבריאות}
\label{subsec:healthcare_challenges}
\begin{english}
    The global healthcare landscape faces unprecedented challenges, including an aging population, the rising prevalence of chronic diseases, increasing costs, and persistent workforce shortages \cite{who2023global}. These factors collectively strain existing healthcare systems, necessitating innovative solutions to maintain and improve patient care quality. Traditional approaches often struggle to keep pace with the demand for personalized, efficient, and accessible medical services. The complexity of modern medicine, coupled with the sheer volume of patient data, further exacerbates these issues, making it difficult for human clinicians to process all relevant information effectively \cite{smith2022data}.

    Moreover, disparities in healthcare access and quality persist across different regions and socioeconomic groups, highlighting the urgent need for scalable and equitable interventions \cite{jones2021equity}. The administrative burden on healthcare professionals also diverts valuable time and resources away from direct patient care, contributing to burnout and reduced efficiency \cite{chen2020burnout}. Addressing these multifaceted challenges requires a paradigm shift in how healthcare is delivered, moving towards more data-driven, proactive, and patient-centric models.
\end{english}

\subsection{הצגת סוכני בינה מלאכותית כפתרון מבטיח}
\label{subsec:ai_agents_introduction}
\begin{english}
    Artificial Intelligence (AI) agents represent a promising avenue for addressing many of the aforementioned challenges in healthcare. These autonomous or semi-autonomous systems are designed to perceive their environment, make decisions, and take actions to achieve specific goals, often mimicking human cognitive functions \cite{russell2010ai}. In healthcare, AI agents can range from sophisticated diagnostic algorithms to personalized treatment recommendation systems and intelligent robotic assistants. Their ability to process vast datasets, identify complex patterns, and learn from experience positions them as powerful tools for augmenting human capabilities and streamlining clinical workflows \cite{lee2023transformative}.

    The integration of AI agents into healthcare is not merely about automation; it is about enhancing precision, efficiency, and accessibility. By automating routine tasks, providing data-driven insights, and supporting complex decision-making, AI agents can free up healthcare professionals to focus on aspects of care that require human empathy, critical thinking, and interpersonal skills. This article explores the transformative potential and inherent challenges of integrating AI agents into various facets of healthcare delivery, from diagnostic assistance and personalized treatment plans to operational efficiency and patient engagement. The significance lies in understanding how these systems can revolutionize patient care while navigating complex societal and clinical landscapes.
\end{english}

