\begin{abstract}
Artificial Intelligence (AI) agents are poised to revolutionize healthcare by enhancing diagnostic accuracy, personalizing treatment, and optimizing operational efficiencies. This article explores their diverse applications, from analyzing complex medical images to streamlining administrative tasks. While AI agents offer unprecedented opportunities to improve healthcare delivery, their successful and ethical deployment depends on robust regulatory frameworks, transparent algorithmic design, and a human-centric approach. Key challenges include addressing algorithmic bias, ensuring data privacy, and establishing clear accountability for AI-driven decisions. The integration of these technologies also necessitates significant investment in infrastructure and the continuous upskilling of healthcare professionals. This article argues that a collaborative human-AI paradigm, supported by comprehensive ethical guidelines, is essential to harness the full potential of AI agents while safeguarding patient safety and promoting equitable access to care.
\end{abstract}

