The primary objective of this article is to explore the burgeoning field of AI agents within healthcare. It focuses on their current applications, their transformative potential, and the complex challenges associated with their integration. The article will delve into the technical, ethical, and regulatory dimensions of deploying autonomous and semi-autonomous AI systems. This comprehensive examination aims to understand how these advanced AI systems can revolutionize healthcare delivery while navigating critical concerns about safety, bias, and human oversight.

